	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="indent(9)"><date>Sunday 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sep. 1851</date></p>
				<p>My Dear Friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The Occident is at hand and I find that I shall have to wait for<lb/> the <date>October</date> No. before my reply comes forth.  You are the best judge in those<lb/> matters&#44; but it seems to me that provided you had the time to get it up&#44; it<lb/> would have been better if it had appeared at the same time as &#8220;<persName>C&#39;s</persName>&#8221;&#8212;however<lb/> you know best&#44; and it might have mutilated against you as a journalist&#44;<lb/> altho it is a query whether the proprietor of a paper should allow a <sic>libellous</sic><lb/> article to appear&#44; when he knows beforehand that it is a libel.</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#8220;Mutilated&#8221; is handwritten.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have no copy of the refutation I sent you.  Will you oblige me<lb/> with a proof at your earliest convenience.  If I had had more time I could have<lb/> answered on several other points&#44; which I think you might introduce into your<lb/> note or remarks&#8212;viz. &#8220;<persName>C</persName>&#8221; starts with the <sic>intetion</sic> of going by the &#8220;Record&#8221;&#8212;<lb/> he had <sic>thesame</sic> opportunity of referring to the record as I had&#8212;<sic>het</sic> he does<lb/> not bring it forward as proof of his assertions&#8212;he <hi rend="underline">positively deceives</hi> you<lb/> into publishing a libel on <hi rend="underline">me</hi>.  I bring the record.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>. Elements of Jewish faith is a deception.  Should<lb/> have been Elements of <persName>Poznanki&#39;s</persName> faithlessness.&#8221;</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#8220;Jewish&#8221; is handwritten.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">3. <persName>S. N. C.</persName> neither <hi rend="underline">painted beautiful pictures</hi> or <hi rend="underline">portraits</hi> from<lb/> imagination&#44; he only prevented a daguerreo <sic>type</sic> view of things as they really are.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">4.  <persName>C.</persName> refers to the Trustees for the truth of his assertion about<lb/> the creed&#8212;and says the Pres. <persName>Mr. O</persName><lb/> at that time was on the Committee.  This is false.  <persName>Mr. O.</persName> was not.  The board<lb/> consisted of</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#8220;Pres. <persName>Mr. O</persName>&#8221; is handwritten.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#8220;The doctrine of a personal Messiah is generally regarded as unfounded<lb/> by our Congregation and as a source of evil to the Jewish nation.&#8221;&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This goes to prove that &#8220;<persName>C</persName>&#8221; makes a fool of himself when he speaks of<lb/> <persName>Dr. E.</persName> touching gratuitously on the vital principle of the Messiah&#44; or that it<lb/> is done to deceive the unwary.  You can use the quotation above&#59; I copied it<lb/> from the original.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>C.</persName> was told <sic>theday</sic> the proof was recd. by <persName>Mr. Moise</persName> and <persName>Mr. Valentine</persName><lb/> that his assertions were false&#44; that <persName>S. N. C.</persName> could bring Documents to prove<lb/> his assertions&#44; yet he did not suppress it&#44; altho he had two weeks to do it in&#8212;<lb/> and the records examine or refer to.  The result has been that the<lb/> party has ceased going to Synagogue as the creed a la <persName>Poznasty</persName> is still on the<lb/> walls&#8212;  Yesterday <persName>Dr. E.</persName> had 4 members in Synagogue.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your remarks are the admiration of everybody.  You hail &#34;<persName>C</persName>&#34; as a firm<lb/> believer in the faith.  <persName>Mr. N. Levin</persName> told me he could prove by <persName>Sol</persName><lb/> that <persName>Isaac Cardozo</persName> exposed himself before him and the sic persons &#34;that<lb/> he did not believe in the bible&#34;&#8212;this is nothing to me&#44; but <persName>Mr. C.</persName> better<lb/> take care how he becomes personal&#44; he lives in open concubinage with a mulatto<lb/> woman by whom he has six illegitimate children&#44; and to this day is running after<lb/> the colored girls&#8212;it is shameful for such a man to insinuate about</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#34;exposed&#34; is handwritten.</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#34;sic persons&#34; is handwritten.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I note your requesting as a favor that you would reply immediately<lb/> to me</p>
